description: Number of unlabeled connected identity interval graphs with n nodes.
references: Hanlon, Phil; Counting interval graphs. Trans. Amer. Math. Soc. 272 (1982), no. 2, 383-426.
R. W. Robinson, Numerical implementation of graph counting algorithms, AGRC Grant, Math. Dept., Univ. Newcastle, Australia, 1980.
N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).
links: R. W. Robinson, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..30
prog: (Sage) def a(n) : return sum(G.is_connected() and G.is_interval() and G.automorphism_group().order()==1 for G in graphs(n)) # _Eric M. Schmidt_, Mar 25 2015
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
extensions: a(21) onwards added by _N. J. A. Sloane_, Oct 19 2006 from the Robinson reference
Definition edited by _Eric M. Schmidt_, Mar 25 2015
